Sokoto State Government has relaxed the 24-hour curfew imposed on the capital city. Governor Aminu Tambuwal, according to a statement by Commissioner for Information, Alhaji Isah Bajini Galadanci, revised the curfew from dusk to dawn in the metropolis. The new order, the Commissioner said, was sequel to the briefing by security heads in the State.   Gunmen burn EEDC, council hqtrs, court, raze 32 vehicles inâ€¦     Atiku, Wike, Saraki, others battle for 3,700 delegates     Police confirm burning of LGA secretariat in Anambra   The Government advised people to maintain peace as it will not condone any breach of law and order in the State . The 24-hour curfew was imposed on Saturday to quell the tension after youths protested demanding the release of two suspects allegedly linked to the killing of Miss Deborah Samuel , a student of the Shehu Shagari College of Education (SSCOE) Sokoto over alleged blasphemy on Thursday.